INSERT INTO articles(id, title, intro, body, category, created_on) VALUES (123456, 'Magic Amino Acids', 'L-Theanine and other goodies', 'Tea is known for its health benefits, which are largely attributed to its antioxidant content. However, tea also contains several amino acids, including L-Theanine, that have been shown to have a range of health benefits.
L-Theanine is an amino acid that is unique to tea and is responsible for the relaxing and calming effect that tea has on the body. L-Theanine has been shown to increase alpha brain wave activity, which is associated with a state of relaxation and mental alertness.
In addition to L-Theanine, tea also contains other beneficial amino acids, such as theanine, arginine, and theobromine. These amino acids have been shown to have a range of health benefits, including improving cognitive function, reducing anxiety, and promoting relaxation.
Theanine is an amino acid that has been shown to improve cognitive function and reduce mental fatigue. Arginine is an amino acid that is important for cardiovascular health, and theobromine is an amino acid that has been shown to have a mild stimulating effect on the body.
While tea is a great source of amino acids, it is important to note that the amount of amino acids in tea can vary depending on the type of tea and the brewing method used. For example, green tea is typically higher in amino acids than black tea.
In conclusion, tea is not only a great source of antioxidants but also contains several beneficial amino acids, including L-Theanine, that have been shown to have a range of health benefits. By incorporating tea into your daily routine, you can enjoy a delicious and healthful beverage that can help promote relaxation, cognitive function, and cardiovascular health.', 'Tea science', '16.03.2023');
